org.cpsolver.instructor.constraints

Class SameInstructorConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cpsolver.ifs.model.Constraint<V,T>
      • org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment.context.ConstraintWithContext<TeachingRequest.Variable,TeachingAssignment,SameInstructorConstraint.Context>
        • org.cpsolver.instructor.constraints.SameInstructorConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Constraint<TeachingRequest.Variable,TeachingAssignment>>, CanHoldContext, HasAssignmentContext<TeachingRequest.Variable,TeachingAssignment,SameInstructorConstraint.Context>

    public class SameInstructorConstraint
extends ConstraintWithContext<TeachingRequest.Variable,TeachingAssignment,SameInstructorConstraint.Context>
    Same Instructor Constraint. Teaching requests linked with this constraint must/should have the same instructor assigned. If discouraged/prohibited, every pair of teaching requests should/must have a different instructor.
    Version:
    IFS 1.3 (Instructor Sectioning)

      • computeConflicts

        public void computeConflicts(Assignment<TeachingRequest.Variable,TeachingAssignment> assignment,
                             TeachingAssignment value,
                             Set<TeachingAssignment> conflicts)
        Description copied from class: Constraint
        The only method which has to be implemented by any constraint. It returns the values which needs to be unassigned in order to make this constraint consistent with the given value if it is assigned to its variable. The computed list of conflicting values is added to the given set of conflicts.
